Our paths ran parallel, beginning with our studies, where we learned to read and analyze texts by the same profesors, and continuing with our interest in the city we were writing about. Each of us followed anthropological paths at our own pace, Aneta veering into the academic side paths, the practice of describing and researching the city through photography, only to find ourselves together again – in the @gridartbub. Today, Aneta is utilizing all her experience curating the architecture program at the Łaźnia Centre for Contemporary Art and Open House Gdańsk. It was wonderful to meet in the studio yesterday to reflect on our journeys from the perspective of the years.</p><p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DViewS6CHN4/">Se slideshow på Instagram</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
